                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="64858" author="sschmidt" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 20:07:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This problem is not just aparent for controller commands but for any command following a rejected command.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64942" author="sschmidt" created="Sun, 3 Apr 2011 15:28:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has been addressed with commit 20ade0afaa2af1aa36acb439e0439746af7048d7. The problem was that the path definition of the controller scaffold command contained &apos;/&amp;#42;&apos; as path which was interpreted as the start of a block comment by the Roo shell. This has been addressed (the shell now checks for block statements by looking for &apos;/&amp;#42;&apos; in combination with &apos;&amp;#42;/&apos;. Furthermore the controller scaffold command will now detect attempted mappings to &apos;/&apos; and &apos;/&amp;#42;&apos; and abort (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/ROO-2268&quot; title=&quot;Controller scaffold command which works for the rootpath.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ROO-2268&quot;&gt;ROO-2268&lt;/a&gt; for discussion).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
